This paper is primarily focused on image aesthetics assessment, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also involves designing a novel architecture to leverage composition information, which could potentially fall under multimedia (cs.MM) or graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. The use of graph convolution for reasoning could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
